about.description:
TorchGeo is a PyTorch domain library, similar to torchvision, providing datasets, samplers, transforms, and pre-trained models specific to geospatial data.

The goal of this library is to make it simple

1. for machine learning experts to work with geospatial data, and
2. for remote sensing experts to explore machine learning solutions.
about.summary: TorchGeo: datasets, samplers, transforms, and pre-trained models for geospatial data

name: torchgeo
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "torchgeo" %}
{% set version = "0.4.1" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/torchgeo-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a3692436bf63df8d2f9b76d16eea5ee309dd1bd74e0fde6e64456abfdb2a5b58

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.7,<4
    - setuptools >=42,<68
  run:
    - einops >=0.3,<0.7
    - fiona >=1.8,<2
    - kornia >=0.6.5,<0.7
    - lightning >=1.8,<3
    - matplotlib-base >=3.3,<4
    - numpy >=1.17.2,<2
    - pillow >=6.2,<10
    - pyproj >=2.2,<4
    - python >=3.7,<4
    - pytorch >=1.12,<3
    - rasterio >=1.0.20,<2
    - rtree >=1,<2
    - scikit-learn >=0.21,<2
    - segmentation-models-pytorch >=0.2,<0.4
    - shapely >=1.3,<3
    - timm >=0.4.12,<0.7
    - torchmetrics >=0.10,<0.12
    - torchvision >=0.13,<0.16

test:
  imports:
    - torchgeo
    - torchgeo.datamodules
    - torchgeo.datasets
    - torchgeo.losses
    - torchgeo.models
    - torchgeo.samplers
    - torchgeo.trainers
    - torchgeo.transforms
  #commands:
  #  - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/microsoft/torchgeo
  doc_url: https://torchgeo.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/microsoft/torchgeo
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'TorchGeo: datasets, samplers, transforms, and pre-trained models for geospatial data'
  description: |
    TorchGeo is a PyTorch domain library, similar to torchvision, providing datasets, samplers, transforms, and pre-trained models specific to geospatial data.

    The goal of this library is to make it simple

    1. for machine learning experts to work with geospatial data, and
    2. for remote sensing experts to explore machine learning solutions.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - adamjstewart
    - calebrob6
